---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import { ArrowRight, Check } from '@lucide/astro';
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
import SplitImageContent from '../components/SplitImageContent.astro';
import ajCallegan from '../assets/images/aj-callegan.jpg';
import aboutImage from '../assets/images/fb2.jpg';
import coupleImage from '../assets/images/beckyandaj.jpg';

const closingQuote = "The answer is almost always there. It's just that the right person hasn't looked for it yet.";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="About AJ & ACC Building Performance"
  description="AJ founded ACC Building Performance to give Gulf South families the honest, documented answers that contractors and doctors have consistently failed to provide."
>
  <section class="hero-airflow hero-noise relative isolate overflow-hidden bg-[#0b4850] px-5 pb-24 pt-36 text-white sm:px-6 lg:px-8 lg:py-32">
    <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto grid max-w-6xl items-center gap-16 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_0.9fr]">
      <div class="text-center lg:text-left">
        <p class="text-[0.62rem] font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[#86c8dc] sm:text-[0.72rem] sm:tracking-[0.34em]">About ACCBP</p>
        <h1 class="mt-4 max-w-4xl text-5xl font-black leading-[0.98] tracking-tight sm:mt-8 sm:text-7xl">Advocate for Healthy Homes</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-lg font-semibold leading-8 text-white/63 sm:mt-8">We started ACC Building Performance performance because sick homes are creating sick families and most of those families have no idea that's what's happening to them.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-[#0f545e] shadow-2xl shadow-black/20">
        <Image src={ajCallegan} alt="AJ Callegan, founder of ACC Building Performance" width={760} class="aspect-[1.02] w-full object-cover object-bottom" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {[
    {
      eyebrow: 'The Story',
      headline: 'How This Work Began',
      body: [
        'AJ has spent his career studying how buildings work, and what happens when they do not. He has seen the same story play out across the Gulf South, in home after home: a family suffering from unexplained illness, cycling through contractors and doctors, spending thousands of dollars on solutions that never hold, being told in one form or another that there is nothing wrong.',
        "There is always something wrong. It's just that most of the professionals who come through those homes aren't trained to find it.",
        'Building science is the discipline of looking at a home as an integrated system: the envelope, the mechanical systems, the moisture dynamics, and how they interact. When AJ began applying building science methodology to residential health assessments, he started finding the answers that had been missed by every prior contractor.',
        "That's what ACC Building Performance was built to do. Not to sell services. Not to generate work. To find the truth about what's happening inside the homes where families live, and to give those families the honest, documented answers they deserve.",
      ],
    },
    {
      eyebrow: 'What Drives This Work',
      headline: 'This Is Personal',
      body: [
        'In 2019, my health took a significant downturn, leading to the unfortunate necessity of selling our HVAC business. Following a diagnosis of epilepsy, I embarked on a challenging medical journey. Eventually, it was revealed that mold toxicity was the root cause of my uncontrollable seizures, a revelation that shed light on the hazards inherent in my career, exposing me to mycotoxins prevalent in HVAC systems and buildings.',
        "Thanks to the intervention of functional medicine, I've been seizure-free for over three years now. Glory to God!! This health ordeal profoundly reshaped my focus and passions. In 2022, I launched a new business centered on building performance, building science, and the house as a system.",
        'Leveraging over two decades of experience and ongoing education, my mission is clear: to address the construction deficiencies that not only led to my illness but contribute to various health issues of others. I aim to drive the necessary changes in building practices, advocating for homes and buildings that are not just safer and more durable but also promote better health and sustainability.',
      ],
    },
    {
      eyebrow: 'Credentials & Expertise',
      headline: 'The Training Behind the Methodology',
      body: [
        "AJ's expertise spans building science, mechanical systems design, construction management, and indoor air quality assessment.",
        'AJ maintains active referral relationships with functional medicine doctors, naturopaths, and integrative health practitioners across the Gulf South. These physicians refer complex, chronically ill patients to ACCBP because AJ provides the environmental documentation their treatment protocols require.',
      ],
      bullets: [
        'Building science certification and training in building performance methodology',
        'Manual J/S/D HVAC design and load calculation',
        'Certified blower door and duct leakage testing',
        'Licensed General Contractor',
        'Extensive field experience in residential assessment, construction oversight, and performance verification across Louisiana, Mississippi, and the Gulf South',
      ],
    },
    {
      eyebrow: 'What You Can Expect',
      headline: "What It's Like to Work With AJ",
      body: [
        "AJ is direct. He won't minimize what he finds, and he won't soften findings to make them easier to hear. If your home has a serious problem, he'll tell you, and he'll explain exactly what it means and what needs to happen about it.",
        'He is also deeply human about this work. He understands that the people who call him are often exhausted, financially strained, and emotionally raw. Every phone call, assessment, and report is delivered with the same commitment: to give you the truth, in plain language, in a way that actually helps you move forward.',
        "No runaround. No generic recommendations. No upsells on things you don't need. Just the honest answer your home, and your family, deserves.",
      ],
    },
  ].map((section, index) => (
    index === 0 ? (
      <SplitImageContent
        section={section}
        index={index}
        image={{ src: coupleImage, alt: 'Close inspection of insulated wall and ceiling assemblies' }}
        variant="full"
      />
    ) : index === 1 ? (
      <section class="relative bg-[linear-gradient(135deg,#0b4850_0%,#073942_48%,#02293c_100%)] px-5 py-24 text-white sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="hero-noise absolute inset-0 opacity-70"></div>
        <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
          <p class="text-[0.68rem] font-black uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-[#65b6ca]">{section.eyebrow}</p>
          <h2 class="mt-5 text-4xl font-black leading-[1.02] tracking-tight text-white sm:text-5xl">{section.headline}</h2>
          <div class="mx-auto mt-9 grid max-w-3xl gap-5 text-left text-base font-semibold leading-7 text-white/75">
            {section.body.map((paragraph) => <p>{paragraph}</p>)}
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    ) : index === 2 ? (
      <section class="bg-acc-mist px-5 py-24 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
          <p class="text-[0.68rem] font-black uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-[#4f93a2]">{section.eyebrow}</p>
          <h2 class="mt-5 text-4xl font-black leading-[1.02] tracking-tight text-acc-ink sm:text-5xl">{section.headline}</h2>
          <div class="mx-auto mt-9 grid max-w-3xl gap-5 text-left text-base font-semibold leading-7 text-[#164f59]/85">
            {section.body.map((paragraph) => <p>{paragraph}</p>)}
          </div>
          {section.bullets && (
            <ul class="mx-auto mt-8 grid max-w-3xl gap-4 text-left">
              {section.bullets.map((bullet) => (
                <li class="flex gap-3 rounded-xl border border-[#d5ded9] bg-white p-5 text-sm font-bold leading-6 text-slate-700 shadow-sm">
                  <Check class="mt-1 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-[#62aebe]" />
                  <span>{bullet}</span>
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          )}
        </div>
      </section>
    ) : index === 3 ? (
      <SplitImageContent
        section={section}
        index={1}
        image={{ src: aboutImage, alt: 'AJ Callegan, founder of ACC Building Performance' }}
        variant="full"
      />
    ) : (
    <section class:list={[
      'relative px-5 py-24 sm:px-6 lg:px-8',
      index % 2 === 0 ? 'bg-acc-mist' : 'bg-[linear-gradient(135deg,#0b4850_0%,#073942_48%,#02293c_100%)] text-white',
    ]}>
      {index % 2 === 1 && <div class="hero-noise absolute inset-0 opacity-70"></div>}
      <div class="relative mx-auto grid max-w-6xl gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[0.42fr_1fr]">
        <div>
          <p class:list={[
            'text-[0.68rem] font-black uppercase tracking-[0.3em]',
            index % 2 === 0 ? 'text-[#4f93a2]' : 'text-[#65b6ca]',
          ]}>{section.eyebrow}</p>
          <h2 class:list={[
            'mt-5 text-4xl font-black leading-[1.02] tracking-tight sm:text-5xl',
            index % 2 === 0 ? 'text-acc-ink' : 'text-white',
          ]}>{section.headline}</h2>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class:list={[
            'grid gap-5 text-base font-semibold leading-7',
            index % 2 === 0 ? 'text-[#164f59]/85' : 'text-white/75',
          ]}>
            {section.body.map((paragraph) => <p>{paragraph}</p>)}
          </div>
          {section.bullets && (
            <ul class="mt-8 grid gap-4">
              {section.bullets.map((bullet) => (
                <li class:list={[
                  'flex gap-3 rounded-xl p-5 text-sm font-bold leading-6 shadow-sm',
                  index % 2 === 0 ? 'border border-[#d5ded9] bg-white text-slate-700' : 'border border-white/12 bg-white/[0.04] text-white/76',
                ]}>
                  <Check class="mt-1 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-[#62aebe]" />
                  <span>{bullet}</span>
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          )}
          {section.quote && (
            <blockquote class:list={[
              'mt-8 rounded-lg p-7 text-xl font-black leading-8 shadow-2xl',
              index % 2 === 0 ? 'bg-[#0b4850] text-white shadow-[#06333a]/25' : 'bg-white text-[#02293c] shadow-black/15',
            ]}>“{section.quote}”</blockquote>
          )}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    )
  ))}

  <section class="bg-acc-mist px-5 py-24 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center">
      <!--<p class="text-[0.68rem] font-black uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-[#62aebe]">The Method</p>-->
      <blockquote class="mt-6 text-4xl font-black leading-[1.08] tracking-tight text-acc-ink sm:text-6xl">
        {closingQuote}
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
